[According to the above information and earlier media-derived reports (eg http://www.kyrgyzkorm.kg/news/zagadochnaya-bolezn-porazhaet-skot-v-kazaxstane.html), LSD started its circulation in the Atyrau region, and probably also in West Kazakhstan, during June 2016 - at least 5 weeks prior to the 1st notification of the disease by the Veterinary Services to the OIE (20160722.4363497), The OIE notification reported LSD diagnosis in the Mangystau region, located southern to the above 2 regions. The 3 apparently infected regions can be seen in the administrative map available at http://tinyurl.com/j4cyqe7.

The vaccine mentioned in the above report is probably the same one applied in the LSD-infected regions of the Russian Federation, namely a heterologous live attenuated vaccine (attenuated sheep pox virus strain "ARRIAH").

Kazakhstan is the world's largest landlocked country, and the 9th largest in the world. The belated diagnosis of LSD there is surprising; following the acquiring of independence in Dec 1991, Kazakhstan obtained support from the West, particularly USA, in the establishment of state-of-the-art laboratories for research and diagnosis of infectious diseases in man and animals. One of the recent research projects addressed capripox vaccines (see ref below).

Early report on the factual distribution of LSD within Kazakhstan is anticipated. Neighbouring countries may take steps to prevent its introduction; those countries include China, Kyrgyzstan and Uzbekistan.

References
Chervyakova OV, Zaitsev VL, Iskakov BK, Tailakova ET, Strochkov VM, Sultankulova KT, Sandybayev NT, Stanbekova GE, Beisenov DK, Abduraimov YO, Mambetaliyev M, Sansyzbay AR, Kovalskaya NY, Nemchinov LG, Hammond RW. Recombinant Sheep Pox Virus Proteins Elicit Neutralizing Antibodies. Viruses. 2016; 8(6): pii: E159. doi: 10.3390/v8060159. Available at http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4926179/ - Mod.AS

